This project is based on a fictional construction SME located near Orléans, operating for over 10 years with a team of around 12–15 employees and a strong reliance on subcontractors.

The company specializes in structural work, renovation, and small industrial building projects, managing approximately 20 to 30 construction sites per year within a 100 km radius.

Over the past three years, the business has experienced steady revenue growth driven by increased demand and project volume. However, this growth has not translated into improved profitability.

The company operates with fragmented Excel-based tracking (sales, invoicing, costs), making it difficult to clearly understand cost structures, monitor cash flow, and identify the true drivers of financial performance.

This project aims to reconstruct a unified view of the business by connecting these data sources, enabling analysis of profitability (EBE), cash collection delays, and hidden cost overruns across projects.